<BLOCKQUOTE>
<!WA12><A HREF="http://found.cs.nyu.edu/projects/"><!WA13><IMG BORDER=0 ALT="What's New" SRC="http://found.cs.nyu.edu/img/homenew.gif"><br></a>
<P>

<FONT SIZE=+1>Ken Perlin won an Academy Award!</FONT>
<P>
<I>(1/6/97)</I> <!WA14><A HREF="http://www.ampas.org/">The Academy of Motion 
Picture Arts & Sciences</A> Board of Governors has voted to
present <!WA15><A HREF=http://found.cs.nyu.edu/perlin>Ken Perlin</A> (our wonderful director) a 
Technical Achievement Award (Academy Certificate) for the
development of "Turbulence," Perlin Noise, a technique used to produce  
natural appearing textures on computer generated surfaces for motion 
picture visual effects.
<P>

<FONT SIZE=+1>New CD released</FONT>
<P>
<I>(1/9/97)</I> <!WA16><A HREF=http://found.cs.nyu.edu/tkbalt>TK Baltimore's</A> college singing group, 
<!WA17><A HREF="http://www.yale.edu/shades">Shades</A>, has just released a new 
album on CD called <!WA18><A 
HREF="http://www.yale.edu/shades/this_year.html#album">"Sisters and 
Brothers."</A> <P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>Techno Seduction</FONT>
<P>
<I>(1/10/97)</I> <!WA19><A HREF="http://cvisions.cat.nyu.edu">Collected 
Visions</A> is included in the exhibition "Techno Seduction" at <!WA20><A 
HREF="http://www.cooper.edu/art/art.html">The
Cooper Union School of Art</A>, 7 E. 7th Street at 3rd Avenue, NYC.  The
opening reception is Thursday January 16 from 6-9 p.m. and the exhibit 
runs from January 17 to February 15, 1997.

